HEADWORD: Reconnoitre
<hw>Rec`on*noi"tre</hw> }</mhw>
<pr>(r?k`?n*noi"t?r)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>reconnoitre</ets>, a former spelling of
<ets>reconna⟦icir⟧tre</ets>. See <er>Recognize</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>To examine with the eye to make a preliminary examination or survey
of; esp., to survey with a view to military or engineering
operations.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To recognize.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Sir
